I love the local neighbourhood vibe of this one off family run eatery that everyone in the neighbourhood seems to know about and are cuisines of. The place is small and unpretentious with three tables each with four chairs. The counter on the right is laden with Dominican specialties which I was told are prepared from scratch and fresh daily. My sampling of the roast chicken and the pigs feet I would attest to the veracity of that, I'm going back to try either the chicken stew or the beef stew tomorrow. Very modest prices for the quality and the natural fruit juice were delightful. I had tamarind, but there is passionfruit and orange also.
